SUMMARY REGISTER: every summary you write here is a brief for the prose writer
who comes later — a later stage (FILL) writes the actual page from it, in a voice
that does not exist yet. A summary is never the page itself. Plain declarative
present tense: who does what, what changes, what it now costs. Name a mood
instead of performing it — "The mentor is dead and the group blames Rell" is a
brief; "grief hangs over the camp like early winter" is prose. Every image you
spend here is stolen from the writer.
